"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-07-23-the-paris-olympics-anti-sex-beds-arent-what-you-think\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"On your mark, get set .\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 23, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 24, \"to\": 25, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 26, \"to\": 27, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"celibacy?\", \"from\": 28, \"to\": 37, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The countdown to the 2024 Summer Olympic Games is officially on, with the opening ceremony in Paris taking place on Friday, June 26.\", \"from\": 39, \"to\": 171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.823157395494568e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, social media has been awash with all sorts of related news - including how the\\\"anti-sex\\\" cardboard bedsfrom the 2020 Games have made a reappearance, with a number of athletes quite literally weighing in on the viral sleep setup.\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"First introduced in the summer of 2021 in Tokyo, Japan, the seemingly flimsy beds, constructed from disposable cardboard, were labeled as \\\"anti-sex\\\" in a reported effort to decrease the risk of COVID-19 transmission.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 453, \"end\": 458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.5530494033290607, \"rank\": 0.8081564959733037, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 460, \"end\": 465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9993359997853489, \"rank\": 0.0006001499252801331, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Beds to be installed in Tokyo Olympic Village will be made of cardboard, this is aimed at avoiding intimacy among athletes,\\\" wrote\\u00a0Team USA Olympic runner Paul Chelimoon X/Twitterat the time.\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.5530494033290607, \"rank\": 0.8081564959733037, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 760, \"end\": 768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.789917824833716e-13, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Beds will be able to withstand the weight of a single person to avoid situations beyond sports.\\\"\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In afollow-up tweet,\\u00a0Chelimo quipped,\\u00a0\\\"At this point I will have to start practicing how to sleep on the floor; cause If my bed collapses and I have no training on sleeping on the floor I am done.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More added stress heading into Tokyo!\\\"\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo!\", \"score\": 0.9999974263529487, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tokyo!\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo!\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo!\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Related  Olympic officials at the time swiftly dispelled the rumor of the bed's flimsiness after Irish gymnast Rhys McClenaghan shareda videoof himself jumping on the bed to test its sturdiness.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"score\": 0.8954436463286748, \"rank\": 0.11534891538371043, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rhys McClenaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thanks for debunking the myth,\\\" the officials tweeted.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You heard it first from @TeamIreland gymnast @McClenaghanRhys - the sustainable cardboard beds are sturdy!\\\"\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today,\\u00a0many have a different perception of COVID's contagiousness, leading some athletes to question the resurgence of the cardboard beds for the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic officials clarified in a recentTikTokwhy the beds are still useful: they are sustainable.\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While they are the same style as used for the Tokyo Olympics, they are \\\"100% made in France\\\" and consist of three \\\"modules\\\" meant to allow athletes to adjust the firmness and length based on their size.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1862, \"end\": 1868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999478537256, \"rank\": 4.365007574158863e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials also noted that the beds would be recycled in France after the Games.\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2036, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999478537256, \"rank\": 4.365007574158863e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A recyclable cardboard bed frame is seen in a room in the Paris 2024 Olympic and Paralympic Village during a press tour in Saint Denis, near Paris, France, June 4, 2024.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3697357071873309e-12, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2142, \"end\": 2160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 2190, \"end\": 2195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Denis\", \"score\": 0.807363869112765, \"rank\": 0.2340168987670291, \"text\": \"Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maurice_Denis\"}, {\"begin\": 2202, \"end\": 2207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.823157395494568e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999478537256, \"rank\": 4.365007574158863e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Gao Jing/Xinhua via Getty Images)On July 20, McClenaghan took to social media once again to sharea videoof himself leaping and somersaulting on his bed, captioning the post, \\\"Paris Oympics 'Anti-sex' beds debunked (again).\\\"\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2252, \"end\": 2257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999999999722604, \"rank\": 1.513881032553473e-11, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After performing a series of moves in which he exerted his full body weight on the mattress in a \\\"rigorous\\\" fashion,\\u00a0McClenaghan claimed, \\\"They passed the test.\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's fake - fake news!\\\"\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2641, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"https://www.instagram.com/p/C9pgQiytQYs/  British springboard diverTom Daleysharedfootageof himself on Instagram showing the beds to his followers, explaining the nooks and crannies of the cardboard contraption - embossed with the phrase\\u00a0\\\"R\\u00eavez vos exploits de demain,\\\" meaning \\\"Dream about your achievements of tomorrow\\\" - and\\u00a0equipped with a mattress, mattress topper \\\"and our own little Paris '24\\\" comforter.\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2685, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999623546507, \"rank\": 3.452303571087804e-08, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2746, \"end\": 2755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9624868918162825e-39, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And as you can see, they are pretty sturdy,\\\" Daley said while jumping around on the bed.\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"https://www.instagram.com/p/C9uFX-ittTV/?hl=en  Rather than serve as sexy-time inhibitors, it would seem that the aim of the beds is to simply be recyclable and more environmentally friendly,as noted by TODAY.\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3356, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, the sustainability underpinning the beds has not stopped some athletes from vocalizing certain comfort-related qualms.\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aleah Finnegan, a Filipino-American gymnast representing the Phillippines, shared ina TikTokthat her bed was \\\"not very soft.\\\"\", \"from\": 3484, \"to\": 3609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3484, \"end\": 3498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleah_Finnegan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aleah Finnegan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleah_Finnegan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleah_Finnegan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are not that comfortable,\\\"\\u00a0she concluded.\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3658, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In aseparate TikTok,Australian water polo player Tilly Kearns stated that the mattress was \\\"rock hard.\\\"\", \"from\": 3660, \"to\": 3763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3673, \"end\": 3679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.694696578160364e-49, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}, {\"begin\": 3715, \"end\": 3721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Kearns\", \"score\": 0.9999944805574595, \"rank\": 5.5194654126258444e-06, \"text\": \"Kearns\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Kearns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Kearns\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A spokesperson from Airweave, the company that makes the mattresses, told TODAY,\\u00a0\\\"Airweave differs from traditional mattresses by containing no springs or foam - we have collaborated with sleep experts and athletes to optimize the performance-enhancing benefits of sleeping on an airweave mattress.\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 4063, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We encourage all athletes to join us at the Mattress Fitting Center in Athletes Village for a personalized consultation, which uses our AI-based MattressFit app to analyze and recommend the best configuration for their body type/needs.\", \"from\": 4065, \"to\": 4301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4137, \"end\": 4153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0493213780626198e-26, \"text\": \"Athletes Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have had the pleasure of positively connecting with hundreds of athletes in Paris already and aim to meet hundreds more.\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4381, \"end\": 4386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.823157395494568e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Not only are Airweave mattresses unique because they are fully customizable,\\\" the spokesperson continued, \\\"the science-backed interwoven design also ensures a firmer sleeping surface that maintains ideal sleeping posture, effortless turning, better distribution of weight, and optimal breathability for longer periods of quality sleep.\\\"\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more  about this topic  Copyright \\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC.\", \"from\": 4766, \"to\": 4827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4812, \"end\": 4821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salon.com\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}, {\"begin\": 4823, \"end\": 4826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999640784780218, \"rank\": 3.5922812564268786e-05, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reproduction of material from any Salon pages without written permission is strictly prohibited.\", \"from\": 4828, \"to\": 4924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4862, \"end\": 4867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.295933144104092e-22, \"text\": \"Salon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SALON \\u00ae is registered in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office as a trademark of Salon.com, LLC.\", \"from\": 4925, \"to\": 5020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5005, \"end\": 5014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salon.com\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"